The paper deals with algorithms for parallel computation on large data, which is a common theme in distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The problems studied, 2-edge connectivity and 2-vertex connectivity, are fundamental problems in graph theory, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves analyzing the running time of algorithms, which is a common theme in algorithms (cs.AL) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
